<TITLE> Apartment prices to rise </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  Apartments will become pricier next year. Finance minister AMA Muhith proposed a flat rate of direct tax at source for the next fiscal's budget on Thursday. Real estate developers will have to pay tax at the time of registration of apartments or buildings. Muhith proposed Tk 185.80 per square feet for apartments at posh residential areas, namely Gulshan Model Town, Banani, Baridhara, DOHS, Dhanmondi, Lalmatia, Uttara, Basundhara, Motijheel, Dilkusha, Dhaka Cantonment and Karwan Bazar, and Khulshi, Agrabad and Panchlaish of Chittagong. For all other areas, realtors will pay tax of Tk 74.32 per square feet. The finance minister said the real estate sector has seen a tremendous growth in recent times but revenue collection from the sector was 'poor'
